Bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{0.5%tsp}. Thinly slice the @closed cup mushrooms{150%g}. Trim the root and the dark green leafy part from the @leek{1}. Halve lengthways then thinly slice. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{2}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

When boiling, add the @rigatoni pasta{200%g} to water and cook until tender, ~{12%minutes}. Once cooked, reserve some of the pasta cooking water (@reserved pasta water{100%ml}), then drain in a #colander{}. Pop back in the pan and drizzle with @oil{drizzle} and stir through to stop it sticking together.

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a #frying pan{} on high heat. Chop any larger plant based 'chicken' pieces in half to give evenly sized pieces and once the pan is hot, add the @Vivera plant chicken pieces{175%g}. Season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{} and stir fry until browned on the outside, ~{4-5%minutes}. Remove to a #bowl{} and pop your pan back on medium high heat. Add a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} if the pan is dry.

Add the mushrooms to the pan and season with @salt{} and @ground black pepper{}. Stir fry until starting to brown, ~{4-5%minutes}. Then add the leek to the pan and cook until soft, another ~{4-5%minutes}. Stir in the garlic and cook for ~{1%minute} more. Pour in the reserved pasta water and @vegetable stock powder{1}, bring to the boil and simmer until reduced by half, ~{2-4%minutes}.

Add the plant based 'chicken' pieces to the pan along with the @creme fraiche{150%g} and stir together. Bring to the boil and simmer until everything is piping hot, ~{3-4%minutes}. Add the drained pasta to the sauce and stir to combine. Taste and add @salt{} and @ground black pepper{} if you feel it needs it. Add a splash of @?water{} if the sauce is too thick.

Serve the pasta in #bowls{} and enjoy!